doc.after: Fossils and the remains of tools show that the Indonesian archipelago was inhabited by Homo erectus popularly known as Java Man between 1 5 million years ago and as recently as 35 000 years ago 17 18 19 Homo sapiens reached the region by around 45 000 years ago 20 In 2011 evidence was uncovered in neighbouring East Timor showing that 42 000 years ago these early settlers were catching and consuming large numbers of big deep sea fish such as tuna 21 and that they had the technology needed to make ocean crossings to reach Australia and other islands
